  "text": "The Third Party Auditor is responsible for the storage of Meta-data of the outsourced files. In our approach, the integrity is checked according to the Meta-data. Meta-data is \"data about data\" [CITATION_1] . We use the Meta-data to describe the outsourced file and it records the information about the size of the file, the number of blocks,the block neighborhood relationship and the inserted random numbers. When legal Data Insertion, Data Deletion or Data Update happens, the corresponding Meta-data will be updated in the Third Party Auditor so that the Meta-data is always correct. All the Data Insertion, Data Deletion or Data Update behaviors will be logged and the log will be kept also in Third Party Auditor.",
